verses.text: When thou sittest to eat with a ruler , consider diligently what \add is\add* before thee:
And put a knife to thy throat , if thou \add be\add* a man given to appetite.
Be not desirous of his dainties : for they \add are\add* deceitful meat. \p
Labour not to be rich : cease from thine own wisdom.

Wilt thou set thine eyes upon that which is not? for \add riches\add* certainly make themselves wings ; they fly away as an eagle toward heaven.\f + \fr 23.5 \ft set…: Heb. cause thine eyes to fly upon\f* \p
Eat thou not the bread of \add him that hath\add* an evil eye , neither desire thou his dainty meats :
For as he thinketh in his heart , so \add is\add* he: Eat and drink , saith he to thee; but his heart \add is\add* not with thee.
The morsel \add which\add* thou hast eaten shalt thou vomit up , and lose thy sweet words.
Speak not in the ears of a fool : for he will despise the wisdom of thy words. \p
Remove not the old landmark ; and enter not into the fields of the fatherless :\f + \fr 23.10 \ft landmark: or, bound\f*
For their redeemer \add is\add* mighty ; he shall plead their cause with thee. \p
Apply thine heart unto instruction , and thine ears to the words of knowledge.
Withhold not correction from the child : for \add if\add* thou beatest him with the rod , he shall not die.
Thou shalt beat him with the rod , and shalt deliver his soul from hell.
My son , if thine heart be wise , my heart shall rejoice , even mine.\f + \fr 23.15 \ft even…: or, even I will rejoice\f*
Yea, my reins shall rejoice , when thy lips speak right things. \p
Let not thine heart envy sinners : but \add be thou\add* in the fear of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* all the day long.
For surely there is an end ; and thine expectation shall not be cut off.\f + \fr 23.18 \ft end: or, reward\f* \p
Hear thou, my son , and be wise , and guide thine heart in the way.
Be not among winebibbers ; among riotous eaters of flesh :\f + \fr 23.20 \ft of flesh: Heb. of their flesh\f*
For the drunkard and the glutton shall come to poverty : and drowsiness shall clothe \add a man\add* with rags.
Hearken unto thy father that begat thee, and despise not thy mother when she is old.
Buy the truth , and sell \add it\add* not; \add also\add* wisdom , and instruction , and understanding.
The father of the righteous shall greatly rejoice : and he that begetteth a wise \add child\add* shall have joy of him.
Thy father and thy mother shall be glad , and she that bare thee shall rejoice.
My son , give me thine heart , and let thine eyes observe my ways.
For a whore \add is\add* a deep ditch ; and a strange woman \add is\add* a narrow pit.
She also lieth in wait as \add for\add* a prey , and increaseth the transgressors among men.\f + \fr 23.28 \ft as for…: or, as a robber\f* \p
Who hath woe ? who hath sorrow ? who hath contentions ? who hath babbling ? who hath wounds without cause ? who hath redness of eyes ?
They that tarry long at the wine ; they that go to seek mixed wine.
Look not thou upon the wine when it is red , when it giveth his colour in the cup , \add when\add* it moveth itself aright.
At the last it biteth like a serpent , and stingeth like an adder.\f + \fr 23.32 \ft an…: or, a cockatrice\f*
Thine eyes shall behold strange women , and thine heart shall utter perverse things.
Yea, thou shalt be as he that lieth down in the midst of the sea , or as he that lieth upon the top of a mast.\f + \fr 23.34 \ft the midst…: Heb. the heart of the sea\f*

They have stricken me, \add shalt thou say, and\add* I was not sick ; they have beaten me, \add and\add* I felt \add it\add* not: when shall I awake ? I will seek it yet again.\f + \fr 23.35 \ft I felt…: Heb. I knew it not\f*
